<br>
Me, asky, and hiyo were working on quests and junk in EW... I get a tell from staboo that lodizal is up and no one is fighting him and to come kill him (or to help his group kill it, I dont remember exactly).  So I tell an xp group to port to iceclad and me/asky/hiyo port to iceclad and run over to the gnoll island.  When we get there you guys were already engaged so we didnt attack.  I got conflicting tells about attacking or not attacking so I never ordered an attack.  There was also lots of ooc and shouts flying about, so I decided best to just sit tight and see what happens.  You all won, and we ported out about 1 minute later.<br>
<br>
There was some discussion about Lodizal getting dispelled.  I don't know who did that, it wasnt us.  I really cant comment on anything else that was said as I wasn't really paying attention or getting involved in those discussions in the least.<br>
<br>
I will say that after having been present for about 10 or so Lodizal killings, they are always ugly like this with lots of fingerpointing and namecalling.  The morale of the story is to convince yourself you are in the right while ensuring that someone under your control gets the xp.  So take that for what its worth... if you think this stuff was bad, you should have seen some of the many WW antics that have occurred over Myga<br>
